SUBSCREEN_TUTORIAL




1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,001
Hello, welcome to SubScreen. Start by pressing the Play button below (>).

2
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:04,000
Good! Playback has been initiated and this line will change to the next one shortly.

3
00:00:04,000 --> 99:99:99,999
Next, try hitting the Next button to the bottom right. We'll wait.

4
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Now hit the Play button below to resume playback.

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:14,000
These buttons can be used if you need
to manually resync the player for
some reason, such as commercials.

6
00:00:14,001 --> 00:00:16,500
This program is capable of automatically

7
00:00:16,501 --> 00:00:19,000
downloading subtitles from OpenSubtitles.org

8
00:00:19,001 --> 00:00:22,000
Just hit the (Download) button, and type
the name of the movie or show.

9
00:00:22,001 --> 00:00:24,500
Optionally, you can login to your OpenSubtitles account

10
00:00:24,501 --> 00:00:27,000
or include only subtitles in a particular language.

11
00:00:27,001 --> 00:00:32,000
Manually downloaded subtitle files should be placed in:
$SUBTITLE_FOLDER_PATH$

12
00:00:32,001 --> 00:00:37,000
Finally, you can use the + or - buttons
to the left in order to adjust text size.

13
00:00:37,001 --> 00:00:42,000
Thank you for downloading this app!

14
00:00:42,001 --> 99:99:99,000
Press the Back button to return
to the file selection menu.